7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 658, L.D. 1664, “An Act to Repeal the
10 Dirigo Business Incentives Program”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'An Act to Amend the Dirigo Business Incentives Program'
13 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
14 following:
15 'Sec. 1. 36 MRSA §5219-AAA, sub-§1, ¶I, as enacted by PL 2023, c. 412, Pt. J,
16 §13, is amended to read:
17 I. "Layoff" means a reduction in workforce at a qualified business with 20 or more
18 persons employed during any one of the preceding 4 quarters that results in an
19 employment loss for at least 2 consecutive months within the same tax year of at least
20 20% of the qualified business's employees in this State. "Layoff" does not mean a
21 reduction in workforce due to a catastrophic event or due to a restriction on the weight
22 or passage of any vehicle over any way by the Department of Transportation pursuant
23 to Title 29-A, section 2395.'
24 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
25 number to read consecutively.
26 SUMMARY
2277 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, replaces the bill and
2288 changes the title. The amendment amends the Dirigo business incentives program by
2299 amending the definition of "layoff" to stipulate "layoff" does not include a reduction in
3300 workforce due to a restriction by the Department of Transportation on the weight or passage
3311 of any vehicle over any way under the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 29-A, section 2395.
